etti, A. Nagaytsev, F. Nerling, D. Neyret, J.\n  Novy, W.-D. Nowak, G. Nukazuka, A.S. Nunes, A.G. Olshevsky, I. Orlov, M.\n  Ostrick, D. Panzieri, B. Parsamyan, S. Paul, J.-C. Peng, F. Pereira, G.\n  Pesaro, M. Pesek, M. Peskova, D.V. Peshekhonov, N. Pierre, S. Platchkov, J.\n  Pochodzalla, V.A. Polyakov, J. Pretz, M. Quaresma, C. Quintans, S. Ramos, C.\n  Regali, G. Reicherz, C. Riedl, N. S. Rogacheva, D.I. Ryabchikov, A. Rybnikov,\n  A. Rychter, R. Salac, V.D. Samoylenko, A. Sandacz, C. Santos, S. Sarkar, I.A.\n  Savin, T. Sawada, G. Sbrizzai, P. Schiavon, H. Schmieden, K. Schoennig, E.\n  Seder, A. Selyunin, L. Silva, L. Sinha, S. Sirtl, M. Slunecka, J. Smolik, A.\n  Srnka, D. Steffen, M. Stolarski, O. Subrt, M. Sulc, H. Suzuki, A. Szabelski,\n  T. Szameitat, P. Sznajder, M. Tasevsky, S. Tessaro, F. Tessarotto, A. Thiel,\n  J. Tomsa, F. Tosello, V. Tskhay, S. Uhl, B.I. Vasilishin, A. Vauth, B. M.\n  Veit, J. Veloso, A.Vidon, M. Virius, S. Wallner, M. Wilfert, J. ter Wolbeek,\n  K. Zaremba, P. Zavada, M. Zavertyaev, E. Zemlyanichkina, N. Zhuravlev, M.\n  Ziembicki","title":"Transverse Extension of Partons in the Proton probed by Deeply Virtual\n  Compton Scattering","comments":"13 pages, 5 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1016/j.physletb.2019.04.038","report-no":"CERN-EP-2018-016","categories":"hep-ex nucl-ex","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We report on the first measurement of exclusive single-photon muoproduction\non the proton by COMPASS using 160 GeV/$c$ polarized $\\mu^+$ and $\\mu^-$ beams\nof the CERN SPS impinging on a liquid hydrogen target. We determine the\ndependence of the average of the measured $\\mu^+$ and $\\mu^-$ cross sections\nfor deeply virtual Compton scattering on the squared four-momentum transfer $t$\nfrom the initial to the final final proton. The slope $B$ of the $t$-dependence\nis fitted with a single exponential function, which yields $B=(4.3 \\ \\pm \\\n0.6_{\\text{stat}}\\_{- \\ 0.3